ink to the comments for the current post in an xml safe way&#10;&#10;@since 3.0.0&#10;@return none" ilk="function" line="200" lineend="202" name="comments_link_feed" returns="none" signature="none comments_link_feed()" /><scope doc="Display the feed GUID for the current comment.&#10;&#10;@package WordPress&#10;@subpackage Feed&#10;@since 2.5.0&#10;&#10;@param int|object $comment_id Optional comment object or id. Defaults to global comment object." ilk="function" line="213" lineend="215" name="comment_guid" signature="comment_guid($comment_id = null)"><variable default="null" ilk="argument" line="213" name="comment_id" /></scope><scope doc="Retrieve the feed GUID for the current comment.&#10;&#10;@package WordPress&#10;@subpackage Feed&#10;@since 2.5.0&#10;&#10;@param int|object $comment_id Optional comment object or id. Defaults to global comment object.&#10;@return bool|string false on failure or guid for comment on success." ilk="function" line="227" lineend="234" name="get_comment_guid" returns="bool" signature="bool get_comment_guid($comment_id = null)"><variable default="null" ilk="argument" line="227" name="comment_id" /><variable citdl="get_comment()" line="228" name="comment" /></scope><scope doc="Display the link to the comments.&#10;&#10;@since 1.5.0" ilk="function" line="241" lineend="243" name="comment_link" signature="comment_link()" /><scope doc="Retrieve the current comment author for use in the feeds.&#10;&#10;@package WordPress&#10;@subpackage Feed&#10;@since 2.0.0&#10;@uses apply_filters() Calls 'comment_author_rss' hook on comment author.&#10;@uses get_comment_author()&#10;&#10;@return string Comment Author" ilk="function" line="256" lineend="258" name="get_comment_author_rss" returns="string" signature="string get_comment_author_rss()" /><scope doc="Display the current comment author in the feed.&#10;&#10;@package WordPress&#10;@subpackage Feed&#10;@since 1.0.0" ilk="function" line="267" lineend="269" name="comment_author_rss" signature="comment_author_rss()" /><scope doc="Display the current comment content for use in the feeds.&#10;&#10;@package WordPress&#10;@subpackage Feed&#10;@since 1.0.0&#10;@uses apply_filters() Calls 'comment_text_rss' filter on comment content.&#10;@uses get_comment_text()" ilk="function" line="280" lineend="284" name="comment_text_rss" signature="comment_text_rss()"><variable citdl="get_comment_text()" line="281" name="comment_text" /></scope><scope doc="Retrieve all of the post categories, formatted for use in feeds.&#10;&#10;All of the categories for the current post in the feed loop, will be&#10;retrieved and have feed markup added, so that they can easily be added to the&#10;RSS2, Atom, or RSS1 and RSS0.91 RDF feeds.&#10;&#10;@package WordPress&#10;@subpackage Feed&#10;@since 2.1.0&#10;@uses apply_filters()&#10;&#10;@param string $type Optional, default is the type returned by get_default_feed().&#10;@return string All of the post categories for displaying in the feed." ilk="function" line="301" lineend="333" name="get_the_category_rss" returns="string" signature="string get_the_category_rss(string $type = null)"><variable citdl="string" default="null" ilk="argument" line="301" name="type" /><variable citdl="string" line="306" name="the_list" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="323" name="cat_name" /><variable citdl="get_the_tags()" line="305" name="tags" /><variable citdl="array()" line="307" name="cat_names" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="313" name="category" /><variable citdl="get_the_category()" line="304" name="categories" /><variable citdl="string" line="309" name="filter" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="317" name="tag" /></scope><scope doc="Display the post categories in the feed.&#10;&#10;@package WordPress&#10;@subpackage Feed&#10;@since 0.71&#10;@see get_the_category_rss() For better explanation.&#10;&#10;@param string $type Optional, default is the type returned by get_default_feed()." ilk="function" line="345" lineend="347" name="the_category_rss" signature="the_category_rss(string $type = null)"><variable citdl="string" default="null" ilk="argument" line="345" name="type" /></scope><scope doc="Display the HTML type based on the blog setting.&#10;&#10;The two possible values are either 'xhtml' or 'html'.&#10;&#10;@package WordPress&#10;@subpackage Feed&#10;@since 2.2.0" ilk="function" line="358" lineend="365" name="html_type_rss" signature="html_type_rss()"><variable citdl="get_bloginfo()" line="359" name="type" /></scope><scope doc="Display the rss enclosure for the current post.&#10;&#10;Uses the global $post to check whether the post requires a password and if&#10;the user has the password for the post. If not then it will return before&#10;displaying.&#10;&#10;Also uses the function get_post_custom() to get the post's 'enclosure'&#10;metadata field and parses the value to display the enclosure(s). The&#10;enclosure(s) consist of enclosure HTML tag(s) with a URI and other&#10;attributes.&#10;&#10;@package WordPress&#10;@subpackage Template&#10;@since 1.5.0&#10;@uses apply_filters() Calls 'rss_enclosure' hook on rss enclosure.&#10;@uses get_post_custom() To get the current post enclosure metadata." ilk="function" line="385" lineend="402" name="rss_enclosure" signature="rss_enclosure()"><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="389" name="val" /><variable citdl="explode()" line="392" name="enclosure" /><variable citdl="t" line="396" name="type" /><variable citdl="preg_split()" line="395" name="t" /><variable line="389" name="key" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="391" name="enc" /></scope><scope doc="Display the atom enclosure for the current post.&#10;&#10;Uses the global $post to check whether the post requires a password and if&#10;the user has the password for the post. If not then it will return before&#10;displaying.&#10;&#10;Also uses the function get_post_custom() to get the post's 'enclosure'&#10;metadata field and parses the value to display the enclosure(s). The&#10;enclosure(s) consist of link HTML tag(s) with a URI and other attributes.&#10;&#10;@package WordPress&#10;@subpackage Template&#10;@since 2.2.0&#10;@uses apply_filters() Calls 'atom_enclosure' hook on atom enclosure.&#10;@uses get_post_custom() To get the current post enclosure metadata." ilk="function" line="421" lineend="433" name="atom_enclosure" signature="atom_enclosure()"><variable citdl="explode()" line="428" name="enclosure" /><variable line="425" name="key" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="425" name="val" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="427" name="enc" /></scope><scope doc="Determine the type of a string of data with the data formatted.&#10;&#10;Tell whether the type is text, html, or xhtml, per RFC 4287 section 3.1.&#10;&#10;In the case of WordPress, text is defined as containing no markup,&#10;xhtml is defined as &quot;well formed&quot;, and html as tag soup (i.e., the rest).&#10;&#10;Container div tags are added to xhtml values, per section 3.1.1.3.&#10;&#10;@link http://www.atomenabled.org/developers/syndication/atom-format-spec.php#rfc.section.3.1&#10;&#10;@package WordPress&#10;@subpackage Feed&#10;@since 2.5&#10;&#10;@param string $data Input string&#10;@return array array(type, value)" ilk="function" line="454" lineend="478" name="prep_atom_text_construct" returns="array" signature="array prep_atom_text_construct(string $data)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="454" name="data" /><variable citdl="xml_get_error_code()" line="461" name="code" /><variable citdl="xml_parser_create()" line="459" name="parser" /></scope><scope doc="Display the link for the currently displayed feed in a XSS safe way.&#10;&#10;Generate a correct link for the atom:self element.&#10;&#10;@package WordPress&#10;@subpackage Feed&#10;@since 2.5" ilk="function" line="489" lineend="492" name="self_link" signature="self_link()"><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="491" name="_SERVER" /><variable line="490" name="host" /></scope><scope doc="Return the content type for specified feed type.&#10;&#10;@package WordPress&#10;@subpackage Feed&#10;@since 2.8.0" ilk="function" line="501" lineend="516" name="feed_content_type" returns="apply_filters()" signature="feed_content_type($type = '')"><variable default="''" ilk="argument" line="501" name="type" /><variable citdl="array()" line="511" name="types" /><variable line="513" name="content_type" /></scope><scope doc="Build SimplePie object based on RSS or Atom feed from URL.&#10;&#10;@since 2.8&#10;&#10;@param mixed $url URL of feed to retrieve. If an array of URLs, the feeds are merged&#10;using SimplePie's multifeed feature.&#10;See also {@link &#8203;http://simplepie.org/wiki/faq/typical_multifeed_gotchas}&#10;&#10;@return WP_Error|SimplePie WP_Error object on failure or SimplePie object on success" ilk="function" line="529" lineend="552" name="fetch_feed" returns="WP_Error" signature="WP_Error fetch_feed(mixed $url)"><variable citdl="mixed" ilk="argument" line="529" name="url" /><variable citdl="SimplePie" line="532" name="feed" /></scope></scope>